HEADWORD: Prosit
<hw>Pro"sit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[L., 3d pers.
sing. subj. present of <ets>prodesse</ets> to do good; <ets>pro</ets>
for + <ets>esse</ets> to be.]</ety> <def>Lit., may it do (you) good; --
a salutation used in well wishing, esp. among Germans, as in drinking
healths; -- also used in the contracted form
<altname>prost</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

